crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a highly sophisticated malicious binary, likely a downloader or backdoor, employing several advanced evasion and obfuscation techniques. Key indicators include: 1) Dynamic API Resolution: It uses hash-based API lookups (djb2 hash constant 0x1505) via functions like sub_4047d0 and sub_404d80 to resolve system calls from kernel32.dll and advapi32.dll at runtime, bypassing static Import Address Table (IAT) analysis. 2) Cryptography: The binary contains a manual implementation of the ChaCha20/Salsa20 stream cipher, evidenced by the standard 'expand 32-byte k' constant in sub_401b60 and associated block-mixing logic in sub_4017e0. 3) Anti-Analysis: It performs environment checks using the CPUID instruction (sub_401e00 and sub_401fe0) to detect virtualization or sandbox environments. 4) Obfuscation: Extensive stack-based string construction and custom decryption loops (e.g., in sub_405cd0 and sub_40fce0) are used to hide command-and-control templates and file paths. 5) Persistence/Injection: The logic involving PEB walking and process parameter manipulation (sub_4058e0) suggests the capability for process hollowing or advanced injection into legitimate Windows processes.
